==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piccadilly
<hw>Pic`ca*dil"ly</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>piccagilles</ets> the
several divisions of pieces fastened together about the brim of the
collar of a doublet, a dim. fr. Sp. <ets>picado</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>picar</ets> to prick. See <er>Pike</er>.]</ety> <def>A high, stiff
collar for the neck; also, a hem or band about the skirt of a garment,
-- worn by men in the 17th century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piccage</ent>⟦br⟧
